1. *Telefonom* sam pozvao mamu juče. (I called my mom on the phone yesterday.)
2. Prošlog meseca sam kupio novi *telefon*. (Last month I bought a new phone.)
3. *Telefonski* poziv je trajao 15 minuta. (The phone call lasted 15 minutes.)
4. Kada *telefoniraš* drugaru? (When are you going to call your friend?)
5. Rekao mi je da će me nazvati *telefonom*. (He told me he will call me on the phone.)
6. *Telefonski* broj firme je 011/123-456. (The company's phone number is 011/123-456.)
7. Često proveravam poruke na *telefonu*. (I often check my messages on the phone.)
8. Juče sam *telefonom* zakazao sastanak. (Yesterday I scheduled a meeting on the phone.)
9. *Telefon* mi je pao i razbio se ekran. (My phone fell and the screen broke.)
10. Pokušaću da ga dobijem *telefonom*. (I will try to reach him on the phone.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "telefonom" is a form of the noun "telefon" (phone) that is used to indicate an action or state related to the phone. The word can also be used as an adverb to indicate the manner in which something is done (e.g. "telefonski poziv" means "phone call").